{"input": ["酒依赖者匿名戒酒会:Alcoholics Anonymous (AA), a self-help group for individuals with alcohol dependency, providing mutual support and professional guidance.", "酒石酸唑吡坦:A drug used for insomnia", "酒类所致精神障碍:Alcohol-induced mental disorders are conditions caused by the effects of ethanol on the central nervous system, either from acute or chronic use", "酒精中毒:酒精中毒是一种可能与性变态伴随发生的疾病", "酒精中毒幻觉症:A condition caused by alcohol intoxication, leading to vivid hallucinations and aggressive behaviors", "酒精依赖者:Individuals who are dependent on alcohol and may suffer from alcohol-induced mental disorders", "酒精或其他物质依赖:A mental health condition accounting for 5% of cases in non-psychiatric departments, often unrecognized in emergency departments", "酒精所致精神障碍:\"酒精所致精神障碍\" (Alcohol-Induced Mental Disorder) refers to a category of mental health conditions directly caused by the consumption of alcohol. These disorders can manifest in various ways, including but not limited to aggressive behaviors and legal issues. The condition arises as a result of prolonged or excessive alcohol use, which disrupts normal brain function and leads to significant psychological and behavioral changes. It is a serious condition that requires medical attention and intervention to address both the mental health symptoms and the underlying alcohol dependency.", "酚噻嗪类药物:酚噻嗪类药物是一类抗精神病药物，广泛用于治疗精神疾病。这类药物以其疗效显著而闻名，但同时也伴随着一些潜在的副作用。其中，最为常见的副作用之一是直立性低血压，即患者在从坐位或卧位突然站起时，可能会感到头晕或晕眩，这是由于血压突然下降所致。此外，酚噻嗪类药物还可能引发药物性皮炎，表现为皮肤出现红斑、瘙痒或其他不适反应。因此，在使用酚噻嗪类药物时，医生通常会密切监测患者的反应，并根据具体情况调整剂量或采取相应的预防措施，以减轻这些副作用的影响。", "酩酊状态:A state of reduced cortical inhibition characterized by decreased consciousness clarity, unstable emotional reactions, increased speech and movement. It can occur during the excited state before coma due to hypnotic drug poisoning, intoxication, or hypoxia."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}